<p>ADMIT</p>
<p>fateri refers to an act of disclosing something in a very general sense, as opposed to celare "to hide".</p>
<p>profiteri refers to a free and spontaneous act of avowal of a belief one holds, unprovoked by questions; and this act is typically proud and assertive.</p>
<p>confiteri refers to an act of confession provoked by questions, threats or the like; and this act is typically contrite.</p>
